<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Aiyre:
[B]First cleric in CH order will always have HUGE aggro.   Some of the times the mob will try to kill you after the ch lands, some of the time not.  If the mob you are fighting starts to run towards you throw on a divine if you can.  Some mobs, however, will promptly summon you and kill you before you even have time to start casting divine aura.  Its just how it works.  If you have an enchanter there, have them cast the aggro spell on the MT and the deaggro spell on you.  Also make sure that the MT has at least one if not two proccing weapons as that will help him gain aggro faster.  
Where other clerics will probably be able to sit and med, you should remain standing for a good amount of time as well.  The other clerics should become aware of the first cleric's possible death and prepared.  
[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
