<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bindol</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">We're in Hate last night, and the decision is made to pull the Maestro of Rancor.  We have the highest warrior be maintank to build up agro before anyone else starts attacking.  I'm the cleric in his group, so it is decided I will be first in the CH chain.<P>The pull occurs, the MT draws the agro, and I start my CH.  CH hits him just as he frenzies, and the Maestro makes a beeline to me and sends me home to my bind spot.<P>Everything else goes off without a hitch and I'm the only death.  The other clerics never even got any agro.<P>After getting rezed back, I ask the coordinating cleric if this is how it was supposed to work.  He said that perhaps I should have been at the limit of my spell range.<P>Now, I wasn't standing with the tank, but I also wasn't standing with the casters.  I was maybe midway between the two.<P>This was my first attempt at an encounter like this, so I figured I'd ask to see what others with more knowledge have to say about it.<P>Bindol Stonehealer<BR>Vicar of Blackwing (Sol Ro)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cland</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm, Bein the first Cleric in the Cheal chain usally isn't a gret thing, you have to be very careful.  <P>Usally Cheal chains start off with a lotta small heals so the first cleric can duck off the first Cheal.<P>I'm no expert I'm just learnin about them so I could be tottally off on this.<P>Also what leel was the tank?  And was he well equiped, a warior in full crafter + what ever he looted on hi first hate raid is gonna need more helas, and more time to get agro that a warrior using defensive discipline in full Keal and primal weapons.<P>My adive to you in that situation is to have both divines up, and tell the tank ahead of time he may ping pong to you.<P>Cland Carbuncle<BR>Lvl 56 Templar, Rallos Zek<P>P.S. I think you were right not sitting with the casters, thats the best way to get AoEd accidently  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Grumbles</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Getting AoE'd by the casters only happens if your cross teaming on a Zek  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>Healing agro in Hate is iffy at best anyways sometimes, being the first cleric to cheal that tank transferred a lot of hate to you and Maestro got mad.  There's 2 other ways you can try to do that, you can try to heal from Max range (or at least farther out) or you can get in close, just next to the tank or right behind the mob.<P>Now MT should be mashing the Taunt button, you cheal, Maestro turns for you, if your right next to Maestro he doesnt walk off and make the MT come find him again.  You pop off Divine Aura and let the tank re-establish agro.  If you were behind Maestro when you chealed MT you can then run just past him and stop right behind MT.  Maestro should see the warrior and start beating on him again.<P>Level is a big factor in pulling agro off of a tank too.  If your 51 or 52 Maestro is a lot more likely to try and kill you mid fight for healing a tank than if your 59 or 60.<P>I always preferred to stay close to boss mobs until I got higher level, that way the tank was still building agro even though I was getting pounded on if they switched.  You should also warn any backup healers to watch the clerics until MT has agro firmly locked in place.<P>Grats on killing Maestro!<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18964" TARGET=_blank>Grumbles</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aiyre</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First cleric in CH order will always have HUGE aggro.   Some of the times the mob will try to kill you after the ch lands, some of the time not.  If the mob you are fighting starts to run towards you throw on a divine if you can.  Some mobs, however, will promptly summon you and kill you before you even have time to start casting divine aura.  Its just how it works.  If you have an enchanter there, have them cast the aggro spell on the MT and the deaggro spell on you.  Also make sure that the MT has at least one if not two proccing weapons as that will help him gain aggro faster.  <BR>Where other clerics will probably be able to sit and med, you should remain standing for a good amount of time as well.  The other clerics should become aware of the first cleric's possible death and prepared.  <P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=24725" TARGET=_blank>Aiyre Soulfyre</A> <BR>High Priest</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serina Moonprism Elay</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am often the first cleric in order. Beucase I am the cleric that makes the order. Anywho, sometimes I get aggro sometimes I don't. Its just a matter of luck and how much the tank has aggro on the mob. Always have your Divine Aura up and ready if you going to be first cleric. Maybe even hit one of them right after your CH goes off to be safe. Point is you never can tell if a mob is gonna come smack you around after you have ch'ed.<P>------------------<BR><B>Serina Moonprism Elay</B><BR>60th High Priestess of Prophecy<BR>Property of Dastran Elay <BR>Member of the Elay Brotherhood<BR>Co-Founder of the Cute Club!<BR>Bertoxx Server<BR><I>"Be kind for everyone you meet is fighting a harder battle."</I>-Plato <BR><I>"Insanity is the root of all genius."</I> -Jen Meyskens</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cyyrae</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have a feeling that Maestro and even Innoruuk's aggro is funny anyway.<P>I was on a raid that had one group with a druid healing.  Clerics were healing main tanks when the group's ranger started to get mashed up a bit.  The druid threw a Superior Heal.  Good old Innoruuk turns, walks over to the poor little druid, ganks her then returns to the fray.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">NightGod</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just curious-why did you even bother setting up a CHeal rotation on Maestro? If it was for practice, I can understand, but he's not really a rotation worthy mob, IMHO.<P>Did him a few days ago with 6 groups and a 57 tank (decent gear, mostly thurg/hate with a few SS thrown in). All the clerics just kept MA targeted and threw a sup/remedy/divine light every so often and watched for enrage/AoE damage (I was in MA group, so I just moved up and used HB to keep damage under control). Think I ended the fight at 60m and the tank at 80h or so with zero deaths. Two weeks ago it was a 53 MA, 40M, 65H, one death from someone who didn't stand on incoming =P<P>------------------<BR>Higar Mettlebender<BR>Vicar of the 53rd Prayer and Luclin Loot Ho<BR>Weilder of the Water Sprinkler of Nem`Ankh<BR>Guardians of the Keep<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20669" TARGET=_blank>Higar's Profile</A><BR>Master Drinker (200) <BR>Master Jeweler (188)Master Fletcher (185)Master Brewer (175) Master Smith (175) Master Potter (168) Master Baker (162) (Anyone got any dragon meat lying around??) Master Tailor (161)<BR>Proud wearer of the 7th prayer shawl.<BR>Coldfyre <BR>Warrior of the 14th Blade<BR>Grandmaster Mule (255) Grandmaster Trader (255) <P>Drinal Server <BR>"These balls are making me testy!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bindol</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for the responses.  It looks like my main mistake was not hitting DA as soon as I saw Maestro turn to me.  I sorta thought that might be the case, but wanted some verification from those with more experience then me.<P>Answering the questions in order that they appear.<P>If I remember right, the tank was 55 or 56.  I'm not sure about his equipment, but I do know that one of our lower level tanks (GFay junky) had a better AC.  I think he also said he had already used his defensive and it was not available.<P>I'm 52, so yeah my level probably had something to do with increasing my agro.<P>As to why the CH rotation, I don't know.  The Hate raid was being run by another guild that my guild does alot of joint raids with.  When they run the raid, we let them call the shots.  So far it has worked out well, since their raid leaders do spend alot time researching things.  <P>I think this was the first time anyone on the raid had gone after Maestro though, so I think he was largely an unknown.  <P>I'm not gonna second guess the decision to use a CH rotation, since we won the battle with only one death (mine).  Hopefully next time I'm in a situation like this, I won't delay on the DA button.<P>Bindol Stonehealer<BR>Vicar of Blackwing (Sol Ro)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
